&lt;h1 id="hiring-is-obsolete"&gt;Hiring is Obsolete&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;May 2005&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(This essay is derived from a talk at the Berkeley CSUA.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The three big powers on the Internet now are Yahoo, Google, and Microsoft. Average age of their founders: 24. So it is pretty well established now that grad students can start successful companies. And if grad students can do it, why not undergrads?&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>